Class AbstractUriPatternProxy

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.poesys.db.dto.AbstractLazyLoadingDtoProxy
      • org.phoenixbioinformatics.api.db.api.AbstractUriPatternProxy
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.poesys.db.dto.IDbDto, com.poesys.db.dto.IObserver, com.poesys.db.dto.ISubject, java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<com.poesys.db.dto.IDbDto>, IUriPattern
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    UriPatternProxy

    public abstract class AbstractUriPatternProxy
extends com.poesys.db.dto.AbstractLazyLoadingDtoProxy
implements IUriPattern

    A data-access layer data-transfer object (DTO) lazy-loading proxy for the UriPattern. This class is an abstract class that contains AndroMDA generated code; change nothing in this class. Instead, override any methods in the concrete subclass generated in the same package. AndroMDA will overwrite this class each time you run it but will never overwrite the concrete subclass.

    A regular expression pattern that specifies a set of URIs

    Author:
    Poesys/DB Cartridge
